history.content: 162 is harder/more work than 61c and 170 is easier/less work than 189. Compared shewchuk's 189 with 162 and 61c with 170, 162 has more work(depends on group) but is easier than 189 and 61c has more work but is easier than 170. Someone said on piazza that Frenkel's 110 does not need to turn in homework. If so, then I think you can handle 170+162+110. Nevertheless, now that you have done well in 189, I don't think you need to take 110.

Can someone who has experience in these 3 courses comment on whether this schedule is doable? I took CS 61C + CS 189 last semester and found it doable (A+ in 61C, A in 189) but can't add on more work (I've used all of the slip days for both classes), is 162 harder/more work than 61C and 170 harder/more work than 189? Also how is the difficulty/workload of 110? Thx so much! (I'm considering dropping 110)
